    dc:description "FIGURE 7. SEM micrographs of the seed coats of Ephedra strongylensis: A. Seed at low magnification (× 15). B. Seed testa at medium magnification (× 50). C. Seed testa at high magnification (× 300). From type material (CAT!)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7473552/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7473548>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Phenological features of Ephedra strongylensis. A. Stromboli near Ginostra (locus classicus), individual in natural habitat with ripe strobili. B. Strombolicchio, male individual in natural habitat. C. Twigs with male cones. D. Twigs with female cones. E. Detail of a ripe strobilus. cones. F. Twigs with ripe strobili. (Photos by S. Cambria)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7473548/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7473554>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. SEM micrographs of pollen grain of Ephedra strongylensis A. Equatorial view (x 2000). B. Polar view (x 2000)." ;
